-- American Airlines cancels 570 Friday flights
-- 
-- Thu Apr 10, 2008 7:01pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/10/us-amr-cancellations-idUSN0946468120080410

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - American Airlines said on Thursday that it has canceled around 570 flights scheduled for Friday as it works to complete the inspections of its MD-80 fleet as required by the Federal Aviation Administration. 

 The airline said that as of Thursday afternoon, 132 MD-80 aircraft were returned to service. On Thursday, American canceled over 930 flights related to the MD-80 inspections. That followed the cancellation of 1,094 flights on Wednesday and 460 canceled flights on Tuesday. (Reporting by Deena Beasley; Editing by  Gary Hill )